Phew... When the labor continues for so many days, it really
starts to take its toll...

One, two, three... No, since we haven't seen the sun,
counting the days here is meaningless...

Section Chief: If you ask me, it's strange enough that you're
still so lively.

Compared to leading a troop on a march, this is nothing...
I'd like to bluff, but with such poor conditions, the
fatigue doesn't fade easily...
Prison Officer: Hey! You rats, it's time to eat! Hmph!
Section Chief: You there, kid. Come over here.
Section Chief: Tsk, I told you two to share it.
You should eat too. Here.

It's okay. I won't do anything bad. Don't hesitate and take
it.

Section Chief: Are you sure? That's quite the bravado. It's not
going to help you.

It doesn't matter. It pains my heart to see a hungry child,
no matter the reason. I can't lose my compassion for those
in weaker positions; it's not how I live.
Section Chief: Way of life, huh...
Section Chief: ──...

Section Chief: You've seen them too while working, haven't you?
The people here.

Section Chief: The circumstances of those thrown in here vary
greatly.

Section Chief: There are those who were thrown in here to work
because they couldn't pay back their debts. Those are still
on the better side of things.

Section Chief: It's an everyday occurrence for those who were
half-killed as punishment for jobs that can't be made public
and then brought here.

Section Chief: Some were sold here at a young age just for a
small amount of money.

Section Chief: There are even those who were captured by
bandits without any fault of their own and sold here to make
money for them.

Section Chief: The weak get preyed upon even in a place like
this. It's a terrible story indeed.

Section Chief: Well, judging by your appearance, you're
probably one of them too...

Section Chief: I don't know who runs this place either, but
it's like the dirty parts of humanity have solidified here.
Section Chief: Nobody comes here because they want to.

Section Chief: That's why we have a rule here not to recklessly
ask about other people's circumstances.

Section Chief: I don't know about your way of life or whatever,
but getting too involved with others will only bring trouble
upon yourself. Here, you think only for yourself.

Section Chief: I've talked too much. Sorry, let's go to sleep.
We can't afford to have problems with the next job...
Ah, that's true...
